1
00:03:58,877 --> 00:04:01,797
Spice for the front page, isn't it?

2
00:04:01,877 --> 00:04:04,797
All you can think of are
headlines for the front page.

3
00:04:04,955 --> 00:04:06,143
Oh, drop it!

4
00:04:06,355 --> 00:04:07,501
Here comes Judge Raghunath.

5
00:04:21,815 --> 00:04:26,618
Such a gentleman! Why on earth
did that goon want to kill him?

6
00:04:26,698 --> 00:04:28,409
Here comes your friend.

7
00:05:00,554 --> 00:05:03,637
Is the jury in place?
- Yes, my Lord. Present.

8
00:05:03,895 --> 00:05:06,244
Is the accused present?
- Present, my Lord.

9
00:05:06,324 --> 00:05:08,276
Who is the counsel for the accused?

10
00:05:13,417 --> 00:05:15,458
Who is the counsel for the accused?

11
00:05:19,13 --> 00:05:21,513
Have you no lawyer
to defend your case?

12
00:05:25,360 --> 00:05:28,140
In that case, the government...
- My Lord.

13
00:05:38,890 --> 00:05:40,764
I'm the counsel for the accused.

14
00:05:47,966 --> 00:05:49,632
I do not wish to defend myself.

15
00:05:50,883 --> 00:05:57,299
I promised to defend you,
if you're ever arraigned. Remember?

16
00:05:58,507 --> 00:06:00,257
Does the accused give his consent?

17
00:06:06,577 --> 00:06:07,632
Yes.

18
00:06:09,842 --> 00:06:16,104
Raj, you have been accused of
a murderous attack on Judge Raghunath.

19
00:06:16,768 --> 00:06:19,299
You may plead your case.

20
00:06:25,910 --> 00:06:29,910
I swear to speak the truth.

21
00:06:32,514 --> 00:06:36,921
Judge Raghunath, can you tell us
why the accused tried to kill you?

22
00:06:37,97 --> 00:06:38,909
Did he have any enmity with you?

23
00:06:40,219 --> 00:06:45,952
Yes. The grudge that a born
felon bears...

24
00:06:46,950 --> 00:06:52,325
against the judge who sentences
him and grants no reprieve.

25
00:06:52,405 --> 00:06:55,25
Could there be no other reason
for such animosity?

26
00:06:55,405 --> 00:06:59,244
None. How else could I relate to him?

27
00:07:02,391 --> 00:07:04,910
I have no further questions.

28
00:07:05,990 --> 00:07:08,522
Defense may proceed with
cross-questioning.

29
00:07:20,319 --> 00:07:23,569
Judge, you are senior to me.

30
00:07:24,281 --> 00:07:28,621
If in the course of questioning,
I happen to affront you do forgive me.

31
00:07:29,888 --> 00:07:33,861
Someone's life is at stake.
And you have taught me...

32
00:07:34,380 --> 00:07:37,444
to ignore all relationships for
the dispensation of justice.

33
00:07:42,69 --> 00:07:46,744
This is my first interrogation.
Please give me your blessings.

34
00:07:52,145 --> 00:07:56,604
What do you mean when you call
the accused a born felon?

35
00:07:57,187 --> 00:07:59,270
He has been a tramp and a hoodlum...

36
00:07:59,645 --> 00:08:01,614
ever since he was a child.
His record says it.

37
00:08:02,432 --> 00:08:05,520
This penchant for crime has surely
been transmitted congenitally.

38
00:08:07,121 --> 00:08:08,811
Judge, do you have any children?

39
00:08:09,144 --> 00:08:10,358
No

40
00:08:10,965 --> 00:08:13,275
But how is this question relevant
to this case?

41
00:08:13,754 --> 00:08:19,983
Most relevant. Think again. Are you
certain that you have no children?

42
00:08:20,642 --> 00:08:25,317
No. But I reiterate. This question...
- Can you recount the circumstance...

43
00:08:25,789 --> 00:08:29,108
when you threw your wife
out of your house?

44
00:08:30,210 --> 00:08:34,631
My Lord, am I to be forced to reply
to such meaningless questions?

45
00:08:35,256 --> 00:08:39,317
Ms Rita, you may ask questions
relevant only to the case.

46
00:08:39,794 --> 00:08:43,410
We wish to know whether or not,
the accused attempted murder.

47
00:08:43,491 --> 00:08:44,919
If yes, then why?

48
00:08:44,999 --> 00:08:49,540
Enough! Stop it! I'm a murderer!
Hang me if you will!

49
00:08:50,679 --> 00:08:52,82
Order! Order!

50
00:08:52,509 --> 00:08:53,957
Proceed with your questioning.

51
00:08:54,814 --> 00:08:58,540
The accused does not deny having
assaulted Judge Raghunath.

52
00:08:58,859 --> 00:09:03,832
But, as you said just now,
the question is why he did it.

53
00:09:04,277 --> 00:09:06,707
This interrogation is meant
to reveal the answer...

54
00:09:07,59 --> 00:09:12,82
if you my Lord, and Judge Raghunath
repose your trust in me for a while

55
00:09:12,839 --> 00:09:14,540
You may proceed.

56
00:09:15,988 --> 00:09:19,669
I repeat my question.
Can you recount the circumstance...

57
00:09:19,749 --> 00:09:22,582
when you threw your wife
out of your house?

58
00:09:23,969 --> 00:09:27,655
I beg your pardon, Judge Raghunath,
but this question is very important.

59
00:09:28,51 --> 00:09:30,415
And not only for the accused.
For you too.

60
00:09:31,40 --> 00:09:34,582
The cause of whatever is happening
today, lies rooted in your past.

61
00:09:36,162 --> 00:09:37,332
Remember?

62
00:09:39,109 --> 00:09:40,332
Remember?

63
00:09:41,374 --> 00:09:45,874
Can you tell us? Why, when
and under what circumstance...

64
00:09:46,332 --> 00:09:48,582
did you throw your wife
out of your house?

65
00:09:49,499 --> 00:09:52,6
