127
00:15:01,6 --> 00:15:04,194
Leave me! Leave me! Leave me!

128
00:15:13,709 --> 00:15:15,810
You heartless bandits!

129
00:15:17,810 --> 00:15:19,310
Where's your chief?

130
00:15:22,187 --> 00:15:25,95
What right have you to terrorise
women from good families?

131
00:15:25,613 --> 00:15:27,822
Aren't you ashamed?
- Ashamed?

132
00:15:27,905 --> 00:15:30,863
Shame is for good folks,
not for bandits and robbers.

133
00:15:31,155 --> 00:15:36,488
As for me, my grandfather was a bandit,
my father was a bandit! But I wasn't.

134
00:15:37,405 --> 00:15:41,738
And your husband went and made me one!
- My husband?

135
00:15:42,405 --> 00:15:46,72
Who are you?
- Jagga. And I was innocent.

136
00:15:46,448 --> 00:15:51,488
But without a shard of evidence,
your husband framed me...

137
00:15:51,822 --> 00:15:55,322
just because my father, my grandfather
were bandits.

138
00:15:55,610 --> 00:15:59,421
He framed me for rape
and he sent me to jail.

139
00:15:59,501 --> 00:16:02,863
So I've decided to prove
your husband right.

140
00:16:07,905 --> 00:16:09,488
Coward!

141
00:16:15,542 --> 00:16:17,322
See what's wrong with her.

142
00:16:19,516 --> 00:16:21,280
Has she come to her senses?

143
00:16:22,67 --> 00:16:26,363
No, she's still in a swoon.

144
00:16:27,277 --> 00:16:32,405
Let her go, Chief. She's pregnant.
She's going to become a mother.

145
00:16:32,779 --> 00:16:36,363
Touch her, and you go to hell.

146
00:16:37,480 --> 00:16:41,562
Pregnant? With a baby?

147
00:16:43,279 --> 00:16:49,656
Her husband said that children born
of good folks turn out good.

148
00:16:50,818 --> 00:16:52,906
And children born of bandits...

149
00:16:54,231 --> 00:16:56,72
turn out to be bandits. Always.

150
00:16:58,482 --> 00:17:03,857
Now let's see what the lawyer's son
turns out to be.

151
00:17:06,234 --> 00:17:09,439
Send her back once she recovers.

152
00:17:11,284 --> 00:17:18,149
Good are those born of good folks!
And of bandits are bandits born.

153
00:17:24,604 --> 00:17:27,478
You should make me a gift.
- What's the occasion?

154
00:17:27,558 --> 00:17:29,808
Not any occasion.
The lady is back.

155
00:17:30,965 --> 00:17:34,87
What did you say? The lady?

156
00:17:34,558 --> 00:17:36,100
Leela!

157
00:17:37,501 --> 00:17:38,975
Leela!

158
00:17:42,225 --> 00:17:43,808
Why is it dark in here?

159
00:17:44,101 --> 00:17:45,770
Nathu! Bansi! Naina!

160
00:17:45,850 --> 00:17:48,350
Lights! Tonight we celebrate!

161
00:17:51,472 --> 00:17:52,725
Leela.

162
00:17:52,808 --> 00:17:57,183
It is you who lights up my life.

163
00:17:57,725 --> 00:17:58,975
Leela.

164
00:18:06,973 --> 00:18:10,517
Now that you're back,
even the lights seem so bright!

165
00:18:10,791 --> 00:18:12,708
Give me the wick.

166
00:18:19,809 --> 00:18:26,225
But Leela, how did you escape?
I hope you weren't in danger?

167
00:18:26,987 --> 00:18:31,483
Your love was with me.
How could anyone even look up at me?

168
00:18:33,682 --> 00:18:37,244
You are tired. Change.
I'll bring you your dressing gown.

169
00:18:44,581 --> 00:18:46,93
These last four days.

170
00:18:51,162 --> 00:18:55,58
The last four days were
like a lifetime.

171
00:18:55,922 --> 00:18:58,392
I took the police and I looked
everywhere for you.

172
00:18:58,695 --> 00:19:00,191
All the while, I feared...

173
00:19:11,125 --> 00:19:16,808
I feared you were in grave danger!

174
00:19:22,554 --> 00:19:27,933
But how did you escape?
And who was this bandit?

175
00:19:28,262 --> 00:19:31,975
Some Jagga.
He said that you had convicted him.

176
00:19:32,493 --> 00:19:34,16
Jagga.

177
00:19:35,35 --> 00:19:41,345
So he escaped to get even with me!
If he has done anything to you...

178
00:19:41,748 --> 00:19:45,908
I'll see to it that he hangs!
- At heart, he's a devil.

179
00:19:46,429 --> 00:19:48,892
But God saved me at the last moment.
Thank God!

180
00:19:51,409 --> 00:19:52,984
Tell me something.

181
00:19:55,319 --> 00:19:56,734
Ask.

182
00:19:57,12 --> 00:20:02,572
Does a bandit's son necessarily
become a bandit?

183
00:20:02,652 --> 00:20:04,901
Yes, it's bound to happen.

184
00:20:08,264 --> 00:20:11,633
But why do you ask?
- Just like that.

185
00:20:22,503 --> 00:20:26,211
Let's see what comes first.
Your becoming a magistrate, or...

186
00:20:27,419 --> 00:20:30,794
Why? Is someone expected?

187
00:20:31,782 --> 00:20:33,336
A new guest.

188
00:20:34,211 --> 00:20:38,211
Now I don't have any chances
of becoming a magistrate.

189
00:20:39,137 --> 00:20:41,168
Why? What happened?

190
00:20:42,503 --> 00:20:46,711
Whatever...
let's talk of something else.

191
00:20:52,753 --> 00:20:54,336
How do you like this?

192
00:20:56,44 --> 00:20:57,378
Nice.

193
00:20:58,306 --> 00:20:59,628
Nice.

194
00:21:00,566 --> 00:21:03,919
Listen...
Are you annoyed with me?

195
00:21:07,378 --> 00:21:10,187
Annoyed? No.

196
00:21:11,336 --> 00:21:13,128
Why should I be annoyed with you?

197
00:21:17,211 --> 00:21:18,941
Have my lunch sent over.

198
00:21:28,285 --> 00:21:30,77
What's the matter?
Where are the servants?

199
00:21:30,160 --> 00:21:34,116
God knows! Maybe they're all dead!
I have to do all the chores.

200
00:21:34,196 --> 00:21:36,574
Let me help you.
- You'd rather tell her all this.

201
00:21:36,655 --> 00:21:38,238
She's sitting around like a queen!

202
00:21:40,363 --> 00:21:43,988
Not to be cross with Leela.
I told her not to strain herself.

203
00:21:44,815 --> 00:21:49,80
You know the condition she is in.
And in a few days from now...

204
00:21:49,160 --> 00:21:53,990
She's going to bear the fruit
of her sins!

205
00:21:54,613 --> 00:21:57,821
What are you saying?!
- What everyone else is saying!

206
00:21:58,280 --> 00:22:02,863
For four days, she lived with a bandit!
And Jagga that!

207
00:22:03,239 --> 00:22:05,857
Don't you remember what
he was convicted for?

208
00:22:07,363 --> 00:22:10,321
Do you enjoy making someone unhappy?
The jaundiced eye sees all yellow.

209
00:22:10,405 --> 00:22:12,988
Do you think you're beyond scrutiny?
Don't you forget...

210
00:22:13,68 --> 00:22:16,113
women have had to stand the test of
chastity. Because society asks for it.

211
00:22:16,193 --> 00:22:17,866
Bhabhi! (Sister-in-law)

212
00:22:22,330 --> 00:22:24,915
Forgive me Bhabhi,
your pot is broken.

213
00:22:25,242 --> 00:22:29,780
It's only an earthen pot. But remember,
a woman's honour is far more fragile.

214
00:22:29,860 --> 00:22:32,71
Once disgraced, her honour
can never be redeemed.

215
00:23:00,259 --> 00:23:03,550
Just answer my question!

216
00:23:03,789 --> 00:23:06,922
Did you not know that your wife
was seeing her lover on the sly?

217
00:23:07,2 --> 00:23:10,807
The villagers used to say that.
But I didn't heed what they said.

218
00:23:11,30 --> 00:23:14,215
You haven't yet told the court
why your wife deserted you.

219
00:23:14,295 --> 00:23:18,23
You know it! Women are adulterous!
- I know what that means!

220
00:23:29,296 --> 00:23:33,615
Raghu, how can you lose
your cool in court?

221
00:23:34,186 --> 00:23:37,657
I'm afraid your chances of
magistrate ship may be clouded.

222
00:23:39,307 --> 00:23:45,282
Chances of a magistrate ship?
That's out of question now.

223
00:23:47,878 --> 00:23:52,610
Can a lawyer whose wife is under
suspicion ever become a magistrate?

224
00:23:52,690 --> 00:23:53,740
Raghu!

225
00:23:53,823 --> 00:23:56,740
The whole town is agog!
- What are you saying?

226
00:23:57,352 --> 00:24:00,740
Aren't you ashamed to talk like this
about your wife?

227
00:24:01,364 --> 00:24:04,311
I'm just saying what everyone is saying.

228
00:24:04,391 --> 00:24:06,198
Let them say what they want.

229
00:24:08,281 --> 00:24:13,364
You're right. That's what I decided.

230
00:24:14,23 --> 00:24:16,231
Let them say what they want.

231
00:24:17,129 --> 00:24:21,786
But how do I get rid of the suspicion?
It's like a leech sucking on...

232
00:24:23,318 --> 00:24:25,720
some dark corner of my mind!
- What now?

233
00:24:45,465 --> 00:24:49,588
Nathu! Naina! Bhabhi!

234
00:24:50,314 --> 00:24:51,754
Where's everyone?

235
00:24:53,903 --> 00:24:55,778
Send Bhabhi over to me.

236
00:24:59,138 --> 00:25:02,436
I am scared.

237
00:25:02,979 --> 00:25:05,700
Why isn't someone coming to me?

238
00:25:06,78 --> 00:25:09,782
That's my husband.
Please, send him over to me.

239
00:25:15,337 --> 00:25:16,616
Look Raghu...

240
00:25:18,645 --> 00:25:21,51
I'm telling you again! That baby
isn't going to be born in this house

241
00:25:21,346 --> 00:25:24,513
If she wants to have her bastard,
let her go elsewhere.

242
00:25:24,593 --> 00:25:27,51
I'm not going to let the honour
of my family be tainted.

243
00:25:27,223 --> 00:25:30,51
I'm going to throw this
wanton woman out!

244
00:25:30,131 --> 00:25:34,208
No! I'm not going anywhere!
No one can take me away from here!

245
00:25:34,288 --> 00:25:39,676
He knows that I'm innocent!
He trusts me, he trusts me!

246
00:25:45,698 --> 00:25:48,885
You're here! Now I'm afraid of no one!

247
00:25:50,379 --> 00:25:53,635
Have you heard?
They want to throw me out!

248
00:25:54,173 --> 00:25:59,93
They say I'm a wanton woman!
They say, I've no right to be here!

249
00:26:00,296 --> 00:26:04,551
But now you're here.
No one will dare anymore.

250
00:26:05,575 --> 00:26:10,874
Tell them I'm untainted!
Tell them you trust me.

251
00:26:12,669 --> 00:26:14,968
Tell them I'm mothering your child.

252
00:26:34,708 --> 00:26:36,702
Have you fallen for what they say?

253
00:26:38,970 --> 00:26:42,819
You're the one who told me...
I don't care for the barking dogs.

254
00:26:44,13 --> 00:26:48,822
If you desert me, who else
in this world can I turn to?

255
00:26:50,269 --> 00:26:53,906
Tell me... tell me that you trust me!

256
00:26:55,668 --> 00:26:57,804
Do you think you're above scrutiny?

257
00:26:57,885 --> 00:27:00,531
Don't you forget women have
had to stand the test of chastity.

258
00:27:15,536 --> 00:27:20,479
Why are you quiet?
Speak... speak!

259
00:27:21,449 --> 00:27:27,354
You can see the state I'm in.
I'm afraid... afraid!

260
00:27:28,444 --> 00:27:33,562
I'm going to become a mother
...the mother of your child.

261
00:27:35,163 --> 00:27:41,119
Have mercy! This is your baby.
This baby is yours!

262
00:27:41,199 --> 00:27:43,99
Get out!
Get out of here!

263
00:27:58,266 --> 00:28:03,599
"A dutiful wife like Sita."

264
00:28:08,598 --> 00:28:14,196
"You gave exile to her."

265
00:28:14,801 --> 00:28:23,130
"Why didn't the earth rip apart?"

266
00:28:25,610 --> 00:28:29,965
"Why didn't the sky rip apart?"

267
00:28:30,955 --> 00:28:35,121
"Women have to endure injustice."

268
00:28:35,202 --> 00:28:39,772
"Women have to endure injustice."

269
00:28:39,852 --> 00:28:43,381
"The dear one of Lord Ram."

270
00:28:43,461 --> 00:28:47,384
"Women have to endure injustice."

271
00:28:47,464 --> 00:28:51,301
"Women have to endure injustice."

272
00:28:51,381 --> 00:28:55,301
"Women have to endure injustice."

273
00:28:55,381 --> 00:28:59,589
"Women have to endure injustice."

274
00:28:59,857 --> 00:29:03,905
"Look, the King of the palace."

275
00:29:03,985 --> 00:29:07,51
"What a game is he playing!"

276
00:29:07,131 --> 00:29:10,339
"What a game is he playing!"

277
00:29:21,690 --> 00:29:25,848
"Look, the King of the palace."

278
00:29:25,928 --> 00:29:28,861
"What a game is he playing!"

279
00:29:28,941 --> 00:29:32,215
"What a game is he playing!"

280
00:29:32,765 --> 00:29:36,884
"From the shell, a pearl,
and in the muck."

281
00:29:36,964 --> 00:29:40,618
"The beautiful lotus is blossoming."

282
00:29:40,698 --> 00:29:44,173
"The beautiful lotus is blossoming."

283
00:29:48,89 --> 00:29:52,89
"Lord, Your ways are strange."

284
00:29:52,169 --> 00:29:56,655
"Lord, Your ways are strange."

285
00:29:56,735 --> 00:30:00,33
"Lord, Your ways are strange."

286
00:30:00,113 --> 00:30:05,75
"Congratulations, Lawyer!
A son has born to you."

287
00:30:05,561 --> 00:30:09,616
Son of a decent family!
Born in a filthy gutter!

288
00:30:12,412 --> 00:30:15,700
"Lord, Your ways are strange."

289
00:30:15,780 --> 00:30:19,536
"Lord, Your ways are strange."

290
00:30:19,616 --> 00:30:23,78
"Lord, Your ways are strange."

291
00:30:23,158 --> 00:30:25,453
Do you not know what your wife
and your son went through...

292
00:30:25,533 --> 00:30:28,918
after you shut your doors on them?
- No

293
00:30:28,998 --> 00:30:30,825
Nor did you try to find out.

294
00:30:32,296 --> 00:30:33,858
But I can tell you.

295
00:30:35,322 --> 00:30:39,24
To get out of your way,
your wife left Lucknow.

296
00:30:40,316 --> 00:30:44,662
And your innocent son grew up
in a Bombay slum.

297
00:30:46,108 --> 00:30:49,108
One day...

298
00:30:57,274 --> 00:30:58,687
Police! Scram!

299
00:31:05,35 --> 00:31:07,21
Greetings, sir.

300
00:31:11,511 --> 00:31:13,979
Hey Nathu...
- Hello, Constable.

301
00:31:15,205 --> 00:31:18,82
What are you up there like a monkey?
Why don't you go to school?

302
00:31:18,355 --> 00:31:22,396
At school, the master asks for fees.

303
00:31:22,878 --> 00:31:26,687
My father hasn't the money
to send me to school.

304
00:31:27,83 --> 00:31:29,937
Look at Leela's son, Raj.
He lives in this slum too.

305
00:31:30,241 --> 00:31:34,271
His mother is worse off. Yet she
sends her boy to such a big school.

306
00:31:35,748 --> 00:31:39,104
What did you say? He isn't a boy.
He's a sissy!

307
00:31:42,229 --> 00:31:47,385
Ma, why do you put oil in my hair?
- Oil keeps the hair soft.

308
00:31:47,624 --> 00:31:50,245
But why do boys in the
neighbourhood call me sissy?

309
00:31:50,325 --> 00:31:53,710
So what?
How do they compare with you?

310
00:31:54,161 --> 00:31:56,510
You're a good boy
who goes to school.

311
00:31:56,809 --> 00:31:59,10
You'll grow up to become
an educated man.

312
00:31:59,299 --> 00:32:02,427
And those vagabonds will go to jail.

313
00:32:03,65 --> 00:32:04,802
Mother, who are called vagabonds?

314
00:32:06,760 --> 00:32:09,83
The ones who just tramp around.

315
00:32:09,733 --> 00:32:11,802
Those who think that whatever
belongs to others, belongs to them.

316
00:32:12,266 --> 00:32:15,666
Those who gamble and drink
instead of going to school.

317
00:32:16,304 --> 00:32:17,624
And they have fun!

318
00:32:19,23 --> 00:32:21,581
Ma, when I grow up,
I'll become vagabond too.

319
00:32:21,874 --> 00:32:26,749
Nonsense! You'll become a lawyer.

320
00:32:28,976 --> 00:32:30,682
Then a magistrate.

321
00:32:31,360 --> 00:32:32,602
And then, a judge.

322
00:32:32,900 --> 00:32:34,193
Raj!

323
00:32:35,265 --> 00:32:36,265
Raj!

324
00:32:38,279 --> 00:32:41,987
You're sitting here?
Everyone's out there buying chocolates.

325
00:32:42,788 --> 00:32:44,386
I don't have money

326
00:32:44,847 --> 00:32:47,306
Why, doesn't your mother
give you money?

327
00:32:47,386 --> 00:32:49,886
Daddy gives me a whole Rupee every day!

328
00:32:50,399 --> 00:32:52,683
You're rich. And I'm poor.

329
00:32:52,763 --> 00:32:55,136
Eat this
- No.

330
00:32:55,452 --> 00:32:57,302
Ma says never ask
for anything to eat.

331
00:32:57,472 --> 00:32:59,886
If she told you not to ask,
go ahead and snatch it.

332
00:33:03,94 --> 00:33:04,52
Wild!

333
00:33:04,453 --> 00:33:06,11
Wild?
- No, no, no.

334
00:33:07,957 --> 00:33:10,469
You're coming to my place
this evening, aren't you?

335
00:33:10,552 --> 00:33:13,437
Why, what's happening?
- My birthday party!

336
00:33:13,518 --> 00:33:15,174
You must come! It's going to be fun!

337
00:33:15,254 --> 00:33:20,52
You know, Daddy has ordered
such a huge cake!

338
00:33:20,136 --> 00:33:23,472
Happy birthday to you!

339
00:33:23,552 --> 00:33:26,802
Happy birthday to you!

340
00:33:32,706 --> 00:33:34,718
Happy birthday to you!

341
00:33:34,799 --> 00:33:36,719
Thank you, thank you, thank you!

342
00:33:36,997 --> 00:33:38,761
Let's go and eat ice cream.

343
00:33:49,176 --> 00:33:52,569
Raj, aren't you giving me a gift?

344
00:33:53,259 --> 00:33:57,111
I didn't have money to buy anything.
I'll give you some other time.

345
00:33:57,509 --> 00:34:00,569
Must you only buy something
to make a gift?

346
00:34:01,704 --> 00:34:05,581
You can give me a flower.
- Really?

347
00:34:12,402 --> 00:34:13,901
Here you are.

348
00:34:14,734 --> 00:34:17,987
Someday, I'm going to make
lots of money.

349
00:34:18,67 --> 00:34:21,484
And I'll buy a gift for you.
Something better than all this.

350
00:34:22,275 --> 00:34:23,525
Do that.

351
00:34:24,192 --> 00:34:26,609
But can anything be better
than this flower?

352
00:34:26,688 --> 00:34:30,24
Ritu! Ritu! Your father
is calling you! - Coming!

353
00:34:30,109 --> 00:34:32,150
Come on Raj, meet my father.

354
00:34:39,920 --> 00:34:41,942
You always say this.

355
00:34:42,25 --> 00:34:44,400
Ritu, say hello to the Judge"

356
00:34:44,734 --> 00:34:46,400
Hello, Judge.

357
00:34:47,161 --> 00:34:48,482
Bless you.

358
00:34:49,237 --> 00:34:53,429
You've grown up in these four years
You must've forgotten me.

359
00:34:55,283 --> 00:34:56,804
Happy birthday

360
00:34:57,594 --> 00:35:02,12
I've just arrived from Lucknow.
I owe you a present.

361
00:35:03,816 --> 00:35:07,636
As of now, I can give you a flower.

362
00:35:09,158 --> 00:35:12,261
Here you are.

363
00:35:15,887 --> 00:35:17,471
Let me put it on your hair.

364
00:35:19,532 --> 00:35:21,887
Someone has already put a flower
over there.

365
00:35:22,143 --> 00:35:24,512
Raj has given me this flower

366
00:35:24,705 --> 00:35:28,11
Daddy, this is Raj.
He's in my class.

367
00:35:28,356 --> 00:35:29,971
I see.
- Hello.

368
00:35:30,54 --> 00:35:32,762
Hello.
- Hello.

369
00:35:34,221 --> 00:35:35,637
God bless you, son"

370
00:35:37,224 --> 00:35:40,336
Raj says that he will become a judge
when he grows up.

371
00:35:40,730 --> 00:35:42,911
Very good!

372
00:35:44,136 --> 00:35:47,137
Your father must be a real gentleman.

373
00:35:48,12 --> 00:35:49,387
What does your father do?

374
00:35:49,563 --> 00:35:53,54
I don't have my father.
I have only my mother

375
00:35:54,968 --> 00:35:57,761
Has he passed away?
- No! Don't say that!

376
00:35:57,851 --> 00:36:02,675
My mother says he is alive.
But...

377
00:36:03,523 --> 00:36:07,988
He doesn't live with you
...and you haven't seen him either?

378
00:36:08,716 --> 00:36:12,299
Your father is a strange man.
- Not a word about my father.

379
00:36:12,795 --> 00:36:15,49
Else... else...

380
00:36:16,724 --> 00:36:18,413
Raj!
- Rita!

381
00:36:21,657 --> 00:36:25,240
How can you let your daughter
play with boys like him?

382
00:36:26,472 --> 00:36:28,41
Go to play, Ritu"

383
00:36:28,781 --> 00:36:32,511
Why, what's wrong with the boy?
I like him.

384
00:36:33,753 --> 00:36:37,774
He doesn't even know his father's
name, and you like him?

385
00:36:38,546 --> 00:36:40,859
I'd say he's just a wastrel
- Forget it.

386
00:36:40,940 --> 00:36:43,274
Must you hang on to
those rotten old ideas?

387
00:36:44,958 --> 00:36:46,649
What was the Bandit's name?

388
00:36:47,619 --> 00:36:48,940
Yes, Jagga.

389
00:36:49,329 --> 00:36:52,649
I remember you saying the same
at his trial.

390
00:36:53,265 --> 00:36:57,232
That a bandit's son
always becomes a bandit.

391
00:36:57,653 --> 00:36:58,939
I still stand by that principle.

392
00:36:59,24 --> 00:37:04,402
Principles, principles and principles!
It's because of these blind dogmas...

393
00:37:04,482 --> 00:37:06,565
that you lost someone
as precious as Leela.

394
00:37:07,357 --> 00:37:09,864
And because of your principles,
you never married again.

395
00:37:10,155 --> 00:37:12,609
The dry parched desert that
your life is, is your own doing.

396
00:37:13,198 --> 00:37:14,524
So much so that you would rather
destroy a friendship...

397
00:37:14,604 --> 00:37:17,314
between two innocent children?
Why, what has the poor child done...

398
00:37:17,395 --> 00:37:19,440
to bring you to harm?

399
00:37:21,221 --> 00:37:22,815
Not this boy. But it was...

400
00:37:23,178 --> 00:37:28,524
someone like him who destroyed my life
...and brought me to disgrace.

401
00:37:29,615 --> 00:37:31,607
Maybe today, he too says
what this boy just said...

402
00:37:32,448 --> 00:37:36,357
I'm only my mother's son
...I have no father.

403
00:37:38,326 --> 00:37:41,649
In every urchin I see him...

404
00:37:43,24 --> 00:37:44,982
the one whom my wife bore,
the one who isn't mine.

405
00:37:46,586 --> 00:37:49,339
My wife's, yet not mine.

406
00:37:51,876 --> 00:37:54,5
Rita looks good in that photo,
doesn't she?

407
00:37:54,278 --> 00:37:57,863
But Ma, why do you work so hard?
This is why you fall ill.

408
00:37:57,943 --> 00:38:00,398
I'm not going to let you work
anymore, you understand?

409
00:38:00,859 --> 00:38:04,904
You mad boy! If I don't work,
how are we going to eat?

410
00:38:04,985 --> 00:38:07,110
I'm a man. I'm the one
who is going to work.

411
00:38:07,517 --> 00:38:09,277
From tomorrow, no going to school!

412
00:38:09,699 --> 00:38:13,27
You won't go to school?
Won't you?

413
00:38:13,963 --> 00:38:16,132
How will you become a gentleman,
unless you educate yourself?

414
00:38:16,212 --> 00:38:18,215
You want to be a vagabond!
- Mother!

415
00:38:20,7 --> 00:38:25,90
Without schooling, how can you become
a lawyer, a magistrate, a judge?

416
00:38:25,959 --> 00:38:33,548
If you say so, I'll go to school
...and I'll work too.

417
00:38:34,131 --> 00:38:38,9
But I won't become a judge.
At Rita's I met a judge.

418
00:38:38,90 --> 00:38:39,556
I didn't like him.

419
00:39:02,480 --> 00:39:06,567
"Go for a stroll, those
who are going."

420
00:39:10,476 --> 00:39:14,937
"Go for a stroll, those
who are going."

421
00:39:15,17 --> 00:39:18,365
"Since when we have been waiting,

422
00:39:18,445 --> 00:39:21,602
we cobblers."

423
00:39:23,508 --> 00:39:25,383
Page 120.

424
00:39:28,633 --> 00:39:29,674
Raj.

425
00:39:29,938 --> 00:39:32,562
Good morning, teacher.
Sorry, I'm late.

426
00:39:32,642 --> 00:39:36,216
I work, you know. I work
- What's all this?

427
00:39:36,300 --> 00:39:41,633
Brush, wax... I give you a good polish.

428
00:39:41,716 --> 00:39:44,424
Your name has been struck
from the rolls.

429
00:39:44,767 --> 00:39:46,924
What?
- You can't study here anymore.

430
00:39:47,5 --> 00:39:51,878
But I've brought the fees too! If you
say so, I'll stop polishing boots.

431
00:39:52,666 --> 00:39:53,758
Silence!

432
00:40:01,215 --> 00:40:03,942
So I can't study here any longer, can I?

433
00:40:04,22 --> 00:40:05,174
No.

434
00:40:06,361 --> 00:40:12,299
For a minute, can I talk to Rita?
I have a gift for her.

435
00:40:12,730 --> 00:40:17,818
Rita's father has transferred her
out of this school. They have moved.

436
00:40:28,512 --> 00:40:30,928
Why did you kick my ball?

437
00:40:31,356 --> 00:40:33,634
Forgive me, I stepped on it by mistake.

438
00:40:33,714 --> 00:40:36,970
How dare a boot-polish-boy?
- Hit him!

439
00:40:38,69 --> 00:40:40,553
Beat him! Beat him!

440
00:40:40,633 --> 00:40:44,53
You're just a boot-polish boy.
You dare take me on?

441
00:40:44,133 --> 00:40:46,845
Beat him! Beat him!

442
00:40:46,925 --> 00:40:48,345
Hit him!

443
00:40:48,428 --> 00:40:53,428
His coat... strip him!

444
00:40:54,472 --> 00:40:56,428
Hit him!

445
00:40:56,928 --> 00:40:59,636
Beat him! Beat him!

446
00:41:01,8 --> 00:41:03,136
Beat him! Beat him!

447
00:41:04,140 --> 00:41:06,220
Beat him! Beat him!

448
00:41:07,763 --> 00:41:10,428
My Ma is ill.
Let me go to my Ma.

449
00:41:10,512 --> 00:41:14,137
You can hit me some other time.
My Ma is ill. Let me go to my Ma.

450
00:41:14,475 --> 00:41:16,348
Your Ma is ill?
- Yes

451
00:41:16,429 --> 00:41:18,610
His Ma is ill!

452
00:41:20,994 --> 00:41:23,12
Run! Uncle Jagga is here! Run!

453
00:41:23,801 --> 00:41:26,136
Run! Uncle Jagga is here! Run!

454
00:41:47,825 --> 00:41:50,57
Get up. Come with me.

455
00:41:55,588 --> 00:41:57,754
Where to?
- Wherever I go.

456
00:41:58,113 --> 00:42:00,462
From now on, you go wherever I go.

457
00:42:01,569 --> 00:42:03,712
That's what your father wanted.

458
00:42:04,640 --> 00:42:07,4
You know my father?
- Yes.

459
00:42:07,895 --> 00:42:09,421
I knew him.

460
00:42:13,640 --> 00:42:17,248
Whatever I am today,
is all thanks to him.

461
00:42:18,285 --> 00:42:21,4
I owe your Dad an old debt.

462
00:42:21,593 --> 00:42:23,687
Then you'll surely help me
find a job somewhere?

463
00:42:23,768 --> 00:42:27,44
Job? What job?
- Whatever! I'll do anything!

464
00:42:27,400 --> 00:42:31,166
My Ma is sick! We haven't anything
to eat! Give me any job!

465
00:42:31,246 --> 00:42:34,183
I'll clean the dishes, sweep floors,
carry luggage... I'll do anything!

466
00:42:34,263 --> 00:42:37,294
Just give me a job! Give me a job!

467
00:42:38,663 --> 00:42:41,305
You fool! Only fools work.

468
00:42:41,637 --> 00:42:44,565
You're a smart boy.
And you talk of working?

469
00:42:44,645 --> 00:42:47,764
Unless I work, how will I eat?
How will I feed my mother?

470
00:42:48,287 --> 00:42:50,680
Steal
- Steal?

471
00:43:00,946 --> 00:43:03,221
Stealing... no!

472
00:43:13,555 --> 00:43:17,346
Yes, yes, yes!
Steal! Steal! Steal!

473
00:43:17,427 --> 00:43:21,26
Pick pockets, locks, rob, kill.

474
00:43:32,555 --> 00:43:34,138
Raj!

475
00:43:38,23 --> 00:43:38,848
Raj!

476
00:43:39,739 --> 00:43:40,701
Raj!

477
00:43:44,56 --> 00:43:45,109
Raj!

478
00:43:45,972 --> 00:43:47,647
You took so long, son.

479
00:43:49,400 --> 00:43:52,764
You've been hungry all day.
Go on, eat food.

480
00:43:53,347 --> 00:43:57,545
Food? Have you cooked?
- Yes, why not?

481
00:43:57,971 --> 00:44:00,264
It's over there, under the plate.

482
00:44:01,4 --> 00:44:04,346
The bread is warm.
I even cooked potatoes.

483
00:44:04,692 --> 00:44:07,476
Take some. It's on the shelf.

484
00:44:17,733 --> 00:44:21,389
Have you found it?

485
00:44:23,490 --> 00:44:25,555
Yes Ma, I found it.

486
00:44:28,365 --> 00:44:30,906
The bread, and potatoes too.

487
00:44:34,666 --> 00:44:37,865
The potatoes are delicious.

488
00:44:38,479 --> 00:44:44,573
Eat it then. Give me a bread too.
I'm very hungry.

489
00:44:45,713 --> 00:44:47,990
Very hungry.
- Bread?

490
00:44:49,703 --> 00:44:52,74
