02:07:38,415 --> 02:07:43,885
"A pain aroused, and my
eyes brimmed with tears."

1226
02:07:43,966 --> 02:07:46,649
"My eyes brimmed with tears."

1227
02:07:49,401 --> 02:07:54,733
"But I remained silent."

1228
02:07:54,816 --> 02:08:00,358
"But I remained silent,
I swear on this sadness."

1229
02:08:00,441 --> 02:08:05,816
"I kept crying, and
I also kept smiling."

1230
02:08:05,899 --> 02:08:12,24
"I kept crying, and
I also kept smiling."

1231
02:08:19,737 --> 02:08:26,662
"When the heart burned,
there was a fire."

1232
02:08:28,60 --> 02:08:33,816
"When my tears flowed, it rained."

1233
02:08:36,228 --> 02:08:44,556
"When the heart burned,
there was a fire."

1234
02:08:44,636 --> 02:08:50,66
"When my tears flowed, it rained."

1235
02:08:50,146 --> 02:08:52,733
"It rained."

1236
02:08:55,633 --> 02:08:58,791
"Like a cloud."

1237
02:09:01,167 --> 02:09:06,611
"Like a cloud, I was a vagabond."

1238
02:09:06,691 --> 02:09:12,191
"I kept crying, and
I also kept smiling."

1239
02:09:12,271 --> 02:09:17,654
"I kept crying, and
I also kept smiling."

1240
02:09:17,734 --> 02:09:23,196
"By falling in love
with you, beloved."

1241
02:09:23,276 --> 02:09:28,739
"By falling in love
with you, beloved."

1242
02:09:28,819 --> 02:09:34,290
"I kept crying, and
I also kept smiling."

1243
02:09:34,370 --> 02:09:40,721
"I kept crying, and
I also kept smiling."

1244
02:09:43,121 --> 02:09:44,454
Raj!

1245
02:09:47,204 --> 02:09:51,7
There you are. Haven't you
brought the police along?

1246
02:09:52,89 --> 02:09:53,996
That bitterness is of no use.

1247
02:09:56,515 --> 02:09:58,163
Your mother has told me everything.

1248
02:10:01,337 --> 02:10:05,674
So you know I'm vagabond,
I've been to jail...

1249
02:10:07,179 --> 02:10:11,329
...and my name is on the police rolls.
Is that what you've come to tell me?

1250
02:10:12,440 --> 02:10:17,623
Try to understand me, Raj.
I still consider you my friend.

1251
02:10:19,299 --> 02:10:20,496
Friend?

1252
02:10:22,646 --> 02:10:29,411
A lawyer's daughter, a judge's ward
takes a tramp for a friend?

1253
02:10:29,933 --> 02:10:33,916
What's your society going to say?
What will your people say?

1254
02:10:34,233 --> 02:10:37,358
If you recant, society
will forgive your past.

1255
02:10:37,708 --> 02:10:41,879
Raj, you can make a new life
for yourself... you can!

1256
02:10:42,950 --> 02:10:46,648
A new life? On what
will I build a new life?

1257
02:10:48,162 --> 02:10:53,41
Can you give me back my childhood,
the education I never had?

1258
02:10:53,880 --> 02:10:59,124
Everyone says that I have no father
to name... I have no honour!

1259
02:10:59,554 --> 02:11:02,926
Can you bring my father back?
Can you give me my name?

1260
02:11:03,354 --> 02:11:08,27
Can you give me my honour?
Tell me... tell me Rita!

1261
02:11:09,589 --> 02:11:10,988
Why are you quiet?

1262
02:11:12,960 --> 02:11:17,738
Rita, I've kept you in the dark.
I've kept myself in the dark.

1263
02:11:19,726 --> 02:11:23,530
Forget me Rita.
Leave me to myself.

1264
02:11:25,25 --> 02:11:26,607
I am not worthy of you.

1265
02:11:27,410 --> 02:11:29,400
You realise fully well,
yet you want to live in this hell.

1266
02:11:29,620 --> 02:11:31,858
I never imagined you'd be so weak.

1267
02:11:32,815 --> 02:11:35,650
Rita, don't you think I never tried
to get out of this hell.

1268
02:11:36,790 --> 02:11:38,775
But tell me, what do I do?

1269
02:11:39,588 --> 02:11:42,483
For twelve years, the world
has chased me towards crime.

1270
02:11:43,416 --> 02:11:45,608
Alone, I cannot face it.

1271
02:11:46,652 --> 02:11:48,733
Alone, I cannot.

1272
02:11:50,137 --> 02:11:53,567
You aren't alone, Raj.
Your mother is with you.

1273
02:11:55,289 --> 02:12:01,317
I'm with you.
- You? With me? With a criminal?

1274
02:12:01,623 --> 02:12:05,383
Yes Raj. With you, forever.

1275
02:12:07,317 --> 02:12:13,000
Good or not, guilty or not,
whatever you are, you're mine.

1276
02:12:16,88 --> 02:12:20,603
This is a matter of the heart. And
the scales of justice cannot judge it.

1277
02:12:23,74 --> 02:12:28,492
But this guilt I carry
with me forever?

1278
02:12:29,859 --> 02:12:32,815
For me, as your wife, it will
be the bride's vermillion.

1279
02:12:38,229 --> 02:12:39,527
Really?

1280
02:12:41,345 --> 02:12:43,583
Come with me.
- Where?

1281
02:12:44,437 --> 02:12:46,396
The Judge wants to meet you.

1282
02:12:48,460 --> 02:12:50,104
The Judge?
- Yes.

1283
02:13:07,817 --> 02:13:08,946
Sit.

1284
02:13:18,604 --> 02:13:19,923
Name?

1285
02:13:20,794 --> 02:13:21,951
Raj.

1286
02:13:22,553 --> 02:13:25,201
Only Raj?
- Yes.

1287
02:13:29,63 --> 02:13:30,284
Your father's name?

1288
02:13:31,783 --> 02:13:33,111
I don't know.

1289
02:13:41,387 --> 02:13:43,719
I see.
What do you do?

1290
02:13:44,643 --> 02:13:48,728
As of now, unemployed.
Like millions of others.

1291
02:13:49,3 --> 02:13:52,40
Any other source of income?
Property?

1292
02:13:55,313 --> 02:13:56,482
Nothing.

1293
02:13:56,781 --> 02:14:01,506
Do you remember polishing boots
when you were a boy?

1294
02:14:02,130 --> 02:14:04,541
I still do.

1295
02:14:04,621 --> 02:14:10,000
And you want to marry Rita?
- Yes. If you allow me.

1296
02:14:10,80 --> 02:14:13,416
And you've been to jail too?
- Rita must've told you that...

1297
02:14:13,496 --> 02:14:17,455
You've recanted? Have you found
another source of making money?

1298
02:14:18,416 --> 02:14:22,621
No.
- But there's still hope, isn't it?

1299
02:14:23,82 --> 02:14:27,580
If some silly rich girl marries you...
- Did you call me here to insult me?

1300
02:14:29,612 --> 02:14:30,913
Judge sir..

1301
02:14:32,930 --> 02:14:34,913
We are in love.

1302
02:14:36,182 --> 02:14:38,742
We want to marry.
- All that I've heard.

1303
02:14:39,972 --> 02:14:41,241
Love!

1304
02:14:43,981 --> 02:14:45,284
Sit.

1305
02:14:46,827 --> 02:14:48,881
And let's talk it over
with a cool head.

1306
02:14:49,414 --> 02:14:52,384
What do you mean?
- I mean that though I don't know...

1307
02:14:52,464 --> 02:14:54,381
..how you managed to seduce
a naive girl..

1308
02:14:55,748 --> 02:14:58,298
..it's clear why you played this trick.

1309
02:14:59,745 --> 02:15:02,214
I want to know what price
you'll take to let her go.

1310
02:15:06,803 --> 02:15:07,970
Judge Raghunath.

1311
02:15:09,470 --> 02:15:14,928
Till today, I thought
I was the worst scoundrel on earth.

1312
02:15:16,405 --> 02:15:19,244
But you turn out to be
one up on me!

1313
02:15:19,324 --> 02:15:22,879
You scum! How dare you use
your filthy colloquy?

1314
02:15:23,282 --> 02:15:26,554
You think I'm going to let
Rita marry a tramp like you?

1315
02:15:27,303 --> 02:15:31,762
She'd rather stay a spinster for life.
Better by far that she dies!

1316
02:15:33,19 --> 02:15:39,811
Why not say that you'd rather
she married some rich big-shot?

1317
02:15:40,644 --> 02:15:44,381
Or maybe, some judge?
- Out of here. Get out.

1318
02:15:59,371 --> 02:16:01,329
Before I leave, I'd like
to ask you a question.

1319
02:16:03,954 --> 02:16:08,701
What if it was your son in my place?
And because he's poor...

1320
02:16:08,781 --> 02:16:15,260
..because he was brought up in the slums
and was forced into crime...

1321
02:16:15,893 --> 02:16:18,357
...what if it was he who was being
denied his love, his life?

1322
02:16:19,310 --> 02:16:21,288
How would you have felt?

1323
02:16:33,655 --> 02:16:34,746
Raj!

1324
02:16:38,538 --> 02:16:40,262
Raj! Raj!

1325
02:16:40,450 --> 02:16:43,290
Jagga has called you.

1326
02:16:43,370 --> 02:16:46,322
There's a big heist.
A bank is to be looted.

1327
02:17:21,977 --> 02:17:23,77
Open the door!

1328
02:17:25,664 --> 02:17:28,250
Open up.
- Who is it?

1329
02:17:28,330 --> 02:17:29,798
Open up!

1330
02:17:31,144 --> 02:17:33,9
Open the door!

1331
02:17:36,563 --> 02:17:37,874
Who is there?
- Open the door!

1332
02:17:45,900 --> 02:17:47,294
Who are you?

1333
02:17:48,948 --> 02:17:50,900
Don't you know me?

1334
02:17:52,755 --> 02:17:54,358
I'm Jagga.

1335
02:17:56,441 --> 02:17:57,691
Jagga!

1336
02:17:58,775 --> 02:18:02,521
The bandit?
- You could say so.

1337
02:18:03,316 --> 02:18:06,629
What do you want here?
- Silence!

1338
02:18:08,775 --> 02:18:11,525
The police are after me.
Where's Raj?

1339
02:18:14,188 --> 02:18:17,355
Get out of my house! I will do nothing
to help someone like you!

1340
02:18:23,150 --> 02:18:29,66
I had you once, and I let you go
Remember the day?

1341
02:18:30,31 --> 02:18:35,650
For twelve years, I cared for your son.
I made his life! For this day?

1342
02:18:35,975 --> 02:18:39,767
Made my son's life?
You forced him into crime.

1343
02:18:40,787 --> 02:18:44,714
Get out of my house. I don't want
your cursed shadow upon my son!

1344
02:18:44,980 --> 02:18:47,529
Get out! Get out of my house!

1345
02:18:47,609 --> 02:18:49,235
Police! Police!

1346
02:18:53,984 --> 02:18:56,862
Go on! Call the police!
- Police!

1347
02:18:56,941 --> 02:19:00,786
Let me see who saves you!
Scream!

1348
02:19:01,236 --> 02:19:02,317
Jagga!

1349
02:19:07,947 --> 02:19:13,67
Will you challenge your boss?
- You're no boss. You're Satan!

1350
02:19:16,584 --> 02:19:18,25
Satan!

1351
02:19:28,281 --> 02:19:30,829
Let's hear what you have to say now.

1352
02:19:55,518 --> 02:19:56,573
Raj!

1353
02:19:59,679 --> 02:20:03,171
Raj! No! No! Mercy!

1354
02:20:06,769 --> 02:20:08,890
No! Enough!

1355
02:20:09,893 --> 02:20:10,942
Jagga!

1356
02:20:44,856 --> 02:20:49,317
What have you done Raj?
- For my sins, this is atonement!

1357
02:21:05,849 --> 02:21:06,884
Police!

1358
02:21:23,885 --> 02:21:25,384
The accused may be presented.

1359
02:21:33,324 --> 02:21:36,887
What's the name of the accused?
- Sir, his name is Raj.

1360
02:21:43,522 --> 02:21:47,349
Father's name?
- Not known, sir. Maybe he has none.

1361
02:21:50,420 --> 02:21:51,629
Order!

1362
02:21:53,315 --> 02:21:58,712
Raj, you have been accused
of killing Jagga.

1363
02:21:59,667 --> 02:22:01,503
Do you have anything to say
in your defence?

1364
02:22:05,102 --> 02:22:08,45
Have you not appointed a lawyer
to defend yourself?

1365
02:22:13,856 --> 02:22:19,425
The case is adjourned. The government
will appoint a counsel for the defence.

1366
02:22:19,505 --> 02:22:24,668
I know the law. Raj killed
in self-defence. That's no crime.

1367
02:22:25,487 --> 02:22:28,961
Please save my Raj, somehow.

1368
02:22:29,49 --> 02:22:32,550
Your deposition is very important.
The whole case hinges on it.

1369
02:22:33,132 --> 02:22:35,981
Come to the court tomorrow.
- All right. Okay, dear.

1370
02:22:55,912 --> 02:22:57,245
Husband!

1371
02:23:02,787 --> 02:23:04,55
She is unconscious.

1372
02:23:04,135 --> 02:23:07,830
Move back! Move! Move!

1373
02:23:08,305 --> 02:23:11,995
Is she dead?
- She has been hurt on the head.

1374
02:23:13,707 --> 02:23:20,662
And Raj killed Jagga
to save my life.

1375
02:23:22,662 --> 02:23:26,495
Please sign here. This deposition
will surely save Raj.

1376
02:23:28,813 --> 02:23:34,162
If Raj is saved, I will be able
to die in peace.

1377
02:23:34,870 --> 02:23:36,449
I should be leaving now.

1378
02:23:49,829 --> 02:23:51,537
Mother!

1379
02:23:51,617 --> 02:23:53,457
My son!
- What happened to you, Ma?

1380
02:23:53,537 --> 02:23:54,665
My son!

1381
02:23:54,745 --> 02:23:59,165
That heartless judge has killed you!
What is his enmity with us?

1382
02:23:59,245 --> 02:24:01,162
You mustn't blame him, son.
- Why not?

1383
02:24:01,656 --> 02:24:03,379
He has always been tying
to make us miserable.

1384
02:24:03,459 --> 02:24:06,287
No son! He is your father.

1385
02:24:08,887 --> 02:24:10,92
My father?

1386
02:24:11,103 --> 02:24:15,79
What are you saying, Ma?
What has come over you?

1387
02:24:16,135 --> 02:24:20,111
I'm not out of my mind, son.
What I'm saying is the truth.

1388
02:24:21,9 --> 02:24:23,120
I could not bring myself
to tell you this until now.

1389
02:24:24,746 --> 02:24:29,762
But if not today, once I'm gone
who else could tell you?

1390
02:24:31,106 --> 02:24:35,438
This can't be, Ma!
This can never be!

1391
02:24:35,518 --> 02:24:40,215
This is a long story.
But I don't have the time.

1392
02:24:41,597 --> 02:24:45,598
Keep this. I'm leaving.

1393
02:24:47,85 --> 02:24:50,579
He will surely recognise you
when you show him this.

1394
02:24:51,950 --> 02:24:55,637
He has never forgiven me.

1395
02:24:56,684 --> 02:25:00,579
But he will surely forgive his son.

1396
02:25:03,536 --> 02:25:06,495
I won't seek mercy from the one
who tortured my mother all her life...

1397
02:25:07,510 --> 02:25:13,120
..the one who made her beg from door
to door. I won't have his mercy!

1398
02:25:14,198 --> 02:25:16,354
Ma, I won't have his mercy!

1399
02:25:16,943 --> 02:25:21,833
If I could see him for
once before I died...

1400
02:25:23,118 --> 02:25:25,133
But why would he come here.

1401
02:25:25,414 --> 02:25:28,274
Come.
- I'm leaving Ma.

1402
02:25:29,177 --> 02:25:30,260
Son!

1403
02:25:30,340 --> 02:25:32,847
I'll avenge you, I will.
- No!

1404
02:25:32,927 --> 02:25:35,94
I'll surely avenge you, I will.
- No, son!.

1405
02:25:35,751 --> 02:25:36,927
Son!

1406
02:25:45,52 --> 02:25:47,385
The Judge is here to see you.

1407
02:25:48,552 --> 02:25:53,688
Which Judge?
- The one whose car ran you over.

1408
02:26:00,680 --> 02:26:04,636
So he has come... before I'm dead.

1409
02:26:05,639 --> 02:26:07,597
Alas, I cannot see.

1410
02:26:09,360 --> 02:26:14,374
Nurse, give him my greetings.

1411
02:26:15,316 --> 02:26:21,139
I am ashamed about the accident.
Please forgive me.

1412
02:26:21,219 --> 02:26:24,597
Forgive you?

1413
02:26:32,30 --> 02:26:33,192
Doctor!

1414
02:27:12,934 --> 02:27:14,59
Mother!

1415
02:27:15,458 --> 02:27:19,329
You didn't die! You were killed!

1416
02:27:20,250 --> 02:27:25,208
That heartless judge has killed you!
To make sure that he isn't exposed!

1417
02:27:49,831 --> 02:27:50,888
Judge sir!

1418
02:28:03,179 --> 02:28:04,287
Judge sir!

1419
02:28:05,323 --> 02:28:07,543
Have you decided the verdict
about the case?

1420
02:28:11,837 --> 02:28:15,975
Case?
- Raj's case.

1421
02:28:17,627 --> 02:28:22,219
You are going mad!
What are you doing to yourself?

1422
02:28:22,994 --> 02:28:25,60
You are a mature, educated woman.

1423
02:28:26,680 --> 02:28:29,125
In a few days, you'll start
going to court as a lawyer.

1424
02:28:29,846 --> 02:28:36,778
You might even make a judge.
If you get emotional over every case...

1425
02:28:37,174 --> 02:28:38,740
..you will never be able to
dispense justice.

1426
02:28:38,820 --> 02:28:42,101
This is not a lawsuit.
It's my life!

1427
02:28:46,253 --> 02:28:50,326
Do you not understand as much?
- Irrespective, it won't alter the law.

1428
02:28:51,426 --> 02:28:53,395
Nor should you let your emotions
come in the way of justice.

1429
02:28:53,476 --> 02:28:57,415
Justice is all I seek.
Raj is completely innocent.

1430
02:28:57,716 --> 02:29:00,305
He killed Jagga tying to save
his mother.

1431
02:29:00,491 --> 02:29:02,972
You can read his mother's
dying declaration.

1432
02:29:04,244 --> 02:29:06,639
In this particular case,
Raj might merit pardon.

1433
02:29:07,491 --> 02:29:10,472
But his whole life is a long story
of involvement with crime and sin.

1434
02:29:11,372 --> 02:29:15,764
I cannot comprehend how you can
sympathise with such a person.

1435
02:29:16,959 --> 02:29:20,97
How can you love him?

1436
02:29:21,234 --> 02:29:22,847
You have studied the law.

1437
02:29:31,519 --> 02:29:35,764
But my heart has not read the laws.

1438
02:29:37,403 --> 02:29:40,472
Heart... and the laws.

1439
02:29:43,396 --> 02:29:47,55
The laws... and the heart.

1440
02:29:49,880 --> 02:29:51,847
What a strange concoction.

1441
02:29:53,645 --> 02:29:55,414
But you are right.

1442
02:29:57,754 --> 02:29:59,680
The heart heeds no laws.

1443
02:30:01,756 --> 02:30:03,847
No laws at all.

1444
02:30:05,821 --> 02:30:06,972
Not even mine.

1445
02:30:26,735 --> 02:30:28,800
No!
- Get out, Rita.

1446
02:30:31,307 --> 02:30:34,139
I'm in a murderous rage!
- Have you gone mad?

1447
02:30:34,936 --> 02:30:37,555
So you have escaped?
- Yes.

1448
02:30:38,917 --> 02:30:40,241
To settle the score with you.

1449
02:30:40,321 --> 02:30:41,76
Raj..

1450
02:30:41,156 --> 02:30:46,680
Then you will be happy to know
that your lawyer...

1451
02:30:48,26 --> 02:30:50,597
...had just convinced me
about your innocence.

1452
02:30:51,687 --> 02:30:54,441
I was inclined to let you off
tomorrow.

1453
02:30:55,268 --> 02:30:57,212
I want no mercy from you.

1454
02:30:57,978 --> 02:31:00,639
I don't want your justice,
your law, nothing!

1455
02:31:01,691 --> 02:31:02,889
All I want...

1456
02:31:06,908 --> 02:31:11,805
Lost your nerve?
You need guts to kill someone.

1457
02:31:12,890 --> 02:31:16,722
You should be thanking the one
who has just saved your life.

1458
02:31:19,733 --> 02:31:22,14
What if I were to use this very knife
to rip your heart out?

1459
02:31:22,513 --> 02:31:24,597
What else can the verdict
of the courts be?

1460
02:31:25,90 --> 02:31:29,550
Judge Raghunath was compelled to kill
a criminal to save his own life.

1461
02:31:29,630 --> 02:31:37,97
Have you gone out of your mind too?
- I was. For a second.

1462
02:31:40,64 --> 02:31:44,347
For the scum that he is,
the hangman's noose will be better.

1463
02:31:47,120 --> 02:31:50,350
Raj. Raj.

1464
02:31:51,907 --> 02:31:54,493
This is the story of
Raj's life and crimes.

1465
02:31:55,197 --> 02:31:59,438
Now you know why and how
he took to crime.

1466
02:32:00,502 --> 02:32:04,673
My Lord, the one who is guilty
is his father...

1467
02:32:04,892 --> 02:32:08,789
..who drove an innocent woman from
his house, and denied his own son.

1468
02:32:09,144 --> 02:32:10,981
He is the one who forced them
to go begging from door to door.

1469
02:32:11,61 --> 02:32:15,554
And in the company of criminals,
he went astray.

1470
02:32:16,228 --> 02:32:18,704
My Lord and members of the Jury...

1471
02:32:18,933 --> 02:32:21,269
..if Raj is to be punished
for his crime..

1472
02:32:21,353 --> 02:32:23,515
..then his father should be
punished too.

1473
02:32:23,595 --> 02:32:26,345
My Lord, I would like to say something.

1474
02:32:27,993 --> 02:32:32,321
Emotion has got the better
of the counsel for defence.

1475
02:32:33,95 --> 02:32:35,672
In her anxiety to save the accused,
the counsel has presented...

1476
02:32:36,803 --> 02:32:40,345
..an interesting story,
however incongruous it might be...

1477
02:32:42,659 --> 02:32:46,398
..to try and prove that
some criminal happens to be my son!

1478
02:32:47,928 --> 02:32:52,931
But I ask, what evidence
does the counsel have?

1479
02:32:53,11 --> 02:32:56,223
No evidence on earth will convince you
that Raj is your son...

1480
02:32:56,303 --> 02:32:58,767
..not unless you are willing
to accept him as your son.

1481
02:32:59,553 --> 02:33:04,362
If there be proof, it lies deep
in your heart and in Raj's eyes.

1482
02:33:04,898 --> 02:33:09,314
Look at him. The same eyes,
the same high brow.

1483
02:33:09,552 --> 02:33:12,789
He even speaks like you speak.
He's just as adamant as you are.

1484
02:33:13,654 --> 02:33:15,970
Are you still not willing
to accept him as your son?

1485
02:33:16,223 --> 02:33:18,648
Ms Rita, the law heeds no emotion.

1486
02:33:19,739 --> 02:33:22,678
Nor my Lord, does the heart
heed any law.

1487
02:33:24,781 --> 02:33:26,223
I have no more to say.

1488
02:33:29,786 --> 02:33:34,77
If the accused has anything to say
in his defence, he may proceed.

1489
02:33:42,435 --> 02:33:48,545
Yes. At last,
after being branded a murderer...

1490
02:33:49,601 --> 02:33:51,897
..I hold your attention.

1491
02:33:53,278 --> 02:33:58,407
Had I been heard earlier, perhaps
I would never have had to stand here.

1492
02:34:00,286 --> 02:34:03,244
Ms Rita has tried her best
to save me from being hanged.

1493
02:34:03,436 --> 02:34:06,502
And not only in this particular case;
in my personal life too.

1494
02:34:06,582 --> 02:34:11,24
In my defence, I wish to say nothing.
I am evil.

1495
02:34:11,967 --> 02:34:13,558
I've been a vagabond ever since
I was a child.

1496
02:34:14,174 --> 02:34:16,175
I'm a murderer, a criminal.

1497
02:34:17,550 --> 02:34:22,300
You may punish me as you please.
But sin, crime, hatred and violence...

1498
02:34:22,383 --> 02:34:25,428
..this vicious circle that holds
your society in a vice-grip...

1499
02:34:25,508 --> 02:34:27,985
..do you think it can be broken
by hanging me?

1500
02:34:28,557 --> 02:34:30,915
I don't want to tell you
the story of my life.

1501
02:34:31,467 --> 02:34:37,337
But all I want to say is, I did not
inherit crime from my parents.

1502
02:34:39,360 --> 02:34:41,303
From that gutter full of filth
that flows beside my shanty...

1503
02:34:41,383 --> 02:34:46,408
...I picked up crime. That gutter
is still flowing over.

1504
02:34:47,633 --> 02:34:50,34
And the virus still breeds.

1505
02:34:52,592 --> 02:34:55,592
And countless children who live
in those slums...

1506
02:34:56,467 --> 02:34:58,481
..are falling prey to the virus
every day.

1507
02:34:59,202 --> 02:35:04,133
Do not think of me. Those children
are the ones you must care for.

1508
02:35:06,336 --> 02:35:08,184
You must care for your children.

1509
02:35:09,688 --> 02:35:12,883
Lest come the day when...
yours...

1510
02:35:13,911 --> 02:35:15,467
..and yours...

1511
02:35:15,794 --> 02:35:17,383
..and yours...

1512
02:35:19,41 --> 02:35:21,425
..and your son too stands
in these docks to reiterate...

1513
02:35:21,505 --> 02:35:24,550
..that it's an honest father's blood
that flows in my veins.

1514
02:35:26,229 --> 02:35:29,758
Time was when I was an innocent boy,
just like your sons.

1515
02:35:31,313 --> 02:35:34,550
Like all mothers, my mother too
wove a golden dream for me.

1516
02:35:37,200 --> 02:35:40,592
She would say, "My son will grow up
to become a lawyer".

1517
02:35:41,923 --> 02:35:48,925
Then he will become a magistrate.
And then, a judge... like his father.

1518
02:35:50,236 --> 02:35:52,383
I know the verdict that this court
is about to give.

1519
02:35:53,650 --> 02:35:58,927
And I'm willing to suffer any sentence.
For my sins, this is atonement.

1520
02:36:00,840 --> 02:36:03,342
But I await the decision
from yet another quarter.

1521
02:36:05,270 --> 02:36:10,217
I want to know Judge Raghunath,
what says your heart?

1522
02:36:11,957 --> 02:36:13,842
What says your heart?

1523
02:36:38,631 --> 02:36:39,608
Raj!

1524
02:37:25,548 --> 02:37:27,936
Has the Judge come to see his convict?

1525
02:37:30,954 --> 02:37:32,297
A father...

1526
02:37:34,590 --> 02:37:35,757
..who is guilty.

1527
02:37:37,623 --> 02:37:39,162
Guilty? You?

1528
02:37:39,242 --> 02:37:40,473
Yes.

1529
02:37:41,789 --> 02:37:44,498
Tomorrow, the law might
pronounce you guilty.

1530
02:37:46,706 --> 02:37:51,301
But in the eyes of God,
I am the one who is guilty.

1531
02:37:54,110 --> 02:37:55,226
Are you weeping?

1532
02:37:56,203 --> 02:38:00,987
Yes, for the father who found his son,
and yet he has lost him.

1533
02:38:01,938 --> 02:38:04,445
For the husband who forced his wife
to become a widow.

1534
02:38:04,525 --> 02:38:07,595
For society, where poverty
breeds crime.

1535
02:38:07,684 --> 02:38:09,600
For the son who is orphaned
though his father is alive.

1536
02:38:09,681 --> 02:38:11,448
For the child who goes through life
looking for someone...

1537
02:38:11,528 --> 02:38:12,944
..who will call him "Son".

1538
02:38:13,314 --> 02:38:14,475
Son.

1539
02:38:17,43 --> 02:38:18,258
Son!

1540
02:38:22,770 --> 02:38:23,839
Son!

1541
02:38:55,964 --> 02:39:01,39
Raj, son of Judge Raghunath,
you have been proved guilty...

1542
02:39:01,119 --> 02:39:03,986
..of tying to assassinate
your father, Judge Raghunath.

1543
02:39:04,453 --> 02:39:08,544
But in the light of the strange and
unfortunate circumstances your life...

1544
02:39:08,913 --> 02:39:12,202
..which your counsel Ms Rita
has presented...

1545
02:39:12,282 --> 02:39:15,688
..you are sentenced to only three years
of rigorous imprisonment.

1546
02:39:53,385 --> 02:39:54,591
Crying?

1547
02:39:55,778 --> 02:39:56,852
You silly girl.

1548
02:39:57,784 --> 02:39:59,252
Silly, lawyers never cry.

1549
02:40:00,195 --> 02:40:01,987
At this rate, how are you
going to practice?

1550
02:40:02,808 --> 02:40:08,529
What use is the practice, Raj?
I wasn't able to save you.

1551
02:40:09,985 --> 02:40:14,309
No Rita, this penance
is very important for me.

1552
02:40:16,178 --> 02:40:18,601
Only after I've been through this,
will I be worthy of you.

1553
02:40:21,61 --> 02:40:23,268
With you beside me,
I can go through anything.

1554
02:40:26,666 --> 02:40:28,161
I will become an honest man.

1555
02:40:29,788 --> 02:40:31,459
Everyone will say I'm a good man.

1556
02:40:33,219 --> 02:40:35,600
I will read, I will write.

1557
02:40:37,661 --> 02:40:41,18
And just like Ma used to say,
first I'll become a lawyer...

1558
02:40:41,936 --> 02:40:43,434
..then a magistrate.

1559
02:40:46,93 --> 02:40:47,134
And then, a judge.

1560
02:40:50,634 --> 02:40:55,767
Last night I saw a judge.
And I liked him.

1561
02:40:58,68 --> 02:41:00,51
I'll become a judge.

1562
02:41:01,878 --> 02:41:04,37
You won't call me a savage anymore,
will you?

1563
02:41:04,341 --> 02:41:06,668
I will. You savage!

1564
02:41:12,21 --> 02:41:13,426
Time up.

1565
02:41:14,792 --> 02:41:16,108
Come on.

1566
02:41:30,940 --> 02:41:32,163
Keep this.

1567
02:41:33,333 --> 02:41:34,801
It's your gift.

1568
02:41:37,71 --> 02:41:39,968
Don't worry. I didn't steal it.

1569
02:41:40,556 --> 02:41:42,429
I just smuggled it in.

1570
02:41:42,773 --> 02:41:43,951
Raj.

1571
02:41:56,505 --> 02:42:02,641
Not your fault, Rita.
It's just the way I look.

1572
02:42:04,644 --> 02:42:05,747
Raj.

1573
02:42:06,315 --> 02:42:07,404
Raj.

1574
02:42:09,218 --> 02:42:15,530
Three years isn't too long, Raj.
I'll wait for you.

1575
02:42:15,757 --> 02:42:16,726
Rita.

1576
02:42:17,508 --> 02:42:20,106
I'll wait for you!
- Don't cry.

1577
02:42:25,659 --> 02:42:30,196
Number 308... move it.

1578
02:42:33,945 --> 02:42:35,168
I should be.

1579
02:42:52,261 --> 02:42:55,26
"I'm not flourishing,
I am not ruined."

1580
02:42:55,106 --> 02:42:57,867
"Still I sing happy songs."

1581
02:42:57,947 --> 02:43:02,2
"Still I sing happy songs."

1582
02:43:02,82 --> 02:43:04,809
"My heart is filled with wounds."

1583
02:43:04,889 --> 02:43:08,318
"But still these lively eyes smile."

1584
02:43:10,782 --> 02:43:13,465
"World.."

1585
02:43:16,447 --> 02:43:22,609
"World, I am troubled by your
sorrows or misfortunes."

1586
02:43:27,757 --> 02:43:33,364
"I am a vagabond."

